    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required credibility levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3; this shortfall is accepted because ASTM F1717 mandates a single standardized test configuration for regulatory submissions and the single-condition data are sufficient to bound the clinical use scenario. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent-difference < 10% acceptance criteria. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible for the stated COU.",
